TYPE
  (*
    We need a target triple and data rep to generate llvm code.
    This is dependant on the target parameter passed in.
    There are only three targets tested and validated below.
    The rest need to be fixed and checked.
    To find a target for your architecture, write a small C program say
    proc.c, and use clang to compile it as clang -c -S -emit-llvm proc.c
    and examine the lines target datalayout and target triple of
    the generated proc.ll file and replace them below as well as set the
    valid entry to true.

    The triple has the general format <arch><sub>-<vendor>-<sys>-<abi>, where:
    arch = x86_64, i386, arm, thumb, mips, etc.
    sub = for ex. on ARM: v5, v6m, v7a, v7m, etc.
    vendor = pc, apple, nvidia, ibm, etc.
    sys = none, linux, win32, darwin, cuda, etc.
    abi = eabi, gnu, android, macho, elf, msvc, etc.

    See the llvm ref manual for the definition of values in the data rep.
  *)

  DT = RECORD
    target, triple, dataRep : TEXT;
    valid : BOOLEAN;
  END;
  ArrDT = ARRAY [0..MaxTargets-1] OF DT;

